Imports System Imports System.Data Imports System.Data.Common Imports System.IO Imports System.Collections.Generic Imports System.Globalization Imports System.Linq Imports Microsoft.VisualBasic Imports System.Windows.Forms Imports OneStream.Shared.Common Imports OneStream.Shared.Wcf Imports OneStream.Shared.Engine Imports OneStream.Shared.Database Imports OneStream.Stage.Engine Imports OneStream.Stage.Database Imports OneStream.Finance.Engine Imports OneStream.Finance.Database Imports System.Deployment.Internal Imports System.Security.Cryptography Imports System.Text Imports System.Text.RegularExpressions
'********************************************************************************************************************************************* 'Author: Jussi Pukki 'Description: Grid view for data audit table with .csv extract functionality. 'Other notes: Most of the SettingsHelpers etc. not currently used, except for the uninstall script which is used to delete solution elements. ' Solution does not create or delete any tables in the database. '*********************************************************************************************************************************************
Namespace OneStream.BusinessRule.DashboardExtender.OP_DA_SolutionHelper Public Class MainClass
'Globals Public RowLimit As Integer = 1000
Public Function Main(ByVal si As SessionInfo, ByVal globals As BRGlobals, ByVal api As Object, ByVal args As DashboardExtenderArgs) As Object Try
Select Case args.FunctionType Case Is = DashboardExtenderFunctionType.LoadDashboard If args.FunctionName.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("OnLoad") Then
If args.LoadDashboardTaskInfo.Reason = LoadDashboardReasonType.Initialize And args.LoadDashboardTaskInfo.Action = LoadDashboardActionType.BeforeFirstGetParameters Then 'Initialize Viewer to appropriate dashboard Dim loadDashboardTaskResult As New XFLoadDashboardTaskResult() loadDashboardTaskResult.ChangeCustomSubstVarsInDashboard = True loadDashboardTaskResult.ModifiedCustomSubstVars.Add("SelectPage_OP_DA", "3_Content_OP_DAM") loadDashboardTaskResult.ModifiedCustomSubstVars.Add("SelectedPage_OP_DA", "Home") loadDashboardTaskResult.ModifiedCustomSubstVars.Add("HelpAboutSolutionCode_OP_DAH", "") loadDashboardTaskResult.ModifiedCustomSubstVars.Add("HelpAboutCreatedBy_OP_DAH", "") loadDashboardTaskResult.ModifiedCustomSubstVars.Add("HelpABoutVersion_OP_DAH", "") loadDashboardTaskResult.ModifiedCustomSubstVars.Add("HelpAboutSolutionTitle_OP_DAH", "")
Return loadDashboardTaskResult End If
End If Case Is = DashboardExtenderFunctionType.ComponentSelectionChanged
If (args.FunctionName.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("Uninstall")) Then 'Standard Setup: Uninstall UI Interface and Solution Data Tables Return Me.UninstallSolution(si, args)
ElseIf (args.FunctionName.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("CreateSolutionTables")) Then Return CreateSolutionTables(si, args)
ElseIf (args.FunctionName.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("DashboardNav")) Then Dim dashboardName As String = args.NameValuePairs.XFGetValue("content", String.Empty) BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.SetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, "SelectPage_OP_DA", dashboardName) If dashboardName.Equals("3_Content_OP_DAM") Then BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.SetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, "SelectedPage_OP_DA", "Home") ElseIf dashboardName.Equals("0_Settings_OP_DAS") Then BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.SetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, "SelectedPage_OP_DA", "Settings") ElseIf dashboardName.Equals("0_Help_OP_DAH") Then BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.SetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, "SelectedPage_OP_DA", "Help") End If
ElseIf (args.FunctionName.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("ValidateSetupStepsExecuted")) Then Return ValidateSetupStepsExecuted(si, args)
ElseIf (args.FunctionName.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("ValidateInputsAndUpdateRowCount")) Then Dim substVars As Dictionary(Of String, String) = args.SelectionChangedTaskInfo.CustomSubstVars Dim dictOrError As DimDictOrError = InitDimDict(si, substVars) If dictOrError.isError Then Dim taskResult As New XFSelectionChangedTaskResult taskResult.IsOK = False taskResult.ShowMessageBox = True taskResult.Message = dictOrError.errorMessage BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.SetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, "RowCount_OP_DA", "") Return taskResult Else Dim rowCount As Integer = GetRowCount(si, substVars) Dim displayString As String = $"{Math.Min(Me.rowLimit, rowCount)} rows of {rowCount.ToString()}" BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.SetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, "RowCount_OP_DA", displayString) End If
ElseIf (args.FunctionName.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("ExtractCsv")) Then Dim substVars As Dictionary(Of String, String) = args.SelectionChangedTaskInfo.CustomSubstVars BRApi.Utilities.QueueDataMgmtSequence(si, "Data Audit (OP_DA) File Extract", substVars)
Dim taskResult As New XFSelectionChangedTaskResult taskResult.ShowMessageBox = True taskResult.Message = $"File extract started in the background. You will find the file in your personal folder (Documents/Users/{StringHelper.RemoveSystemCharacters(si.UserName,False,False)}/DataAudit_Extract.csv) when ready." Return taskResult
Else 'This code sets up a TaskResult value Dim taskResult As New XFSelectionChangedTaskResult taskResult.ChangeCustomSubstVarsInDashboard = True taskResult.Message = "Unknown Function encounterd" Return taskResult End If End Select
Return Nothing Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, ex)) End Try End Function
#Region "OP_DA Custom Functions"
Public Function GetRowCount(si As SessionInfo, substVars As Dictionary(Of String, String)) As Integer Try 'Collect list of filtered member IDs per dimension into a dict Dim DictOrError As DimDictOrError = InitDimDict(si, substVars) If DictOrError.isError Then Return Nothing End If Dim DimDict As Dictionary(Of String, List(Of String)) = DictOrError.DimDict
'Generate SQL where clauses based on the member ID lists Dim Conditions As Object = GenerateWhereClauses(si, DimDict, substVars) Dim WhereClause As String = Conditions.WhereClause Dim ParamsList As List(Of dbParamInfo) = Conditions.ParamsList
'Get total row count for filtered data set and update dashboard parameter. Dim sqlc As String = $" SELECT COUNT(*) As Rows FROM DataEntryAuditCell WITH (NOLOCK) JOIN DataEntryAuditSource ON DataEntryAuditCell.AuditSourceID = DataEntryAuditSource.UniqueID {WhereClause} "
Dim dtc As DataTable Using dbConn As DBConnInfo = BRApi.Database.CreateApplicationDbConnInfo(si) dtc = BRAPi.Database.ExecuteSql(dbConn, sqlc.ToString, ParamsList, False) End Using
Dim rowCount As Integer = dtc.Rows(0)("Rows") Return rowCount Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, ex)) End Try End Function
Public Function GetDataAuditTable(si As SessionInfo, substVars As Dictionary(Of String, String), Optional ignoreRowLimit As Boolean = False) As DataTable Try 'Collect list of filtered member IDs per dimension into a dict Dim DictOrError As DimDictOrError = InitDimDict(si, substVars) If DictOrError.isError Then Return Nothing End If Dim DimDict As Dictionary(Of String, List(Of String)) = DictOrError.DimDict
'Generate SQL where clauses based on the member ID lists Dim Conditions As Object = GenerateWhereClauses(si, DimDict, substVars) Dim WhereClause As String = Conditions.WhereClause Dim ParamsList As List(Of dbParamInfo) = Conditions.ParamsList
'Hard coded maximum, never try to load the whole table to dashboard. 'Extract can ignore this, it should run through DM job and output a file to fileshare. 'Dim RowLimit As Integer = 1000
'Generate SQL select clause considering the row limit Dim selectClause As String If ignoreRowLimit Then selectClause = "SELECT" Else selectClause = "SELECT TOP (@ROWLIMIT)" End If ParamsList.Add(New DbParamInfo("ROWLIMIT", Me.RowLimit))
'Get main data table. 'Use TOP in SELECT. Because of ORDER BY, DB still has to materialize entire result set. 'Transferring large amount of data from the database seems to take significant time, however. Dim sql As String = $" {selectClause} DataEntryAuditCell.Timestamp, DataEntryAuditSource.UserId, CubeId, EntityId, ConsId, ScenarioId, TimeId, ( CASE WHEN DataEntryAuditCell.IsViewYTD = 1 THEN 'YTD' ELSE 'Periodic' END ) AS 'View', AccountId, FlowId, OriginId, ICId, UD1Id, UD2Id, UD3Id, UD4Id, UD5Id, UD6Id, UD7Id, UD8Id, Amount, LAG(Amount, 1) OVER ( PARTITION BY CubeId, EntityId, ConsId, ScenarioId, TimeId, AccountId, FlowId, OriginId, ICid, UD1Id, UD2Id, UD3Id, UD4Id, UD5Id, UD6Id, UD7Id, UD8Id ORDER BY DataEntryAuditCell.Timestamp ASC ) PreviousAmount, IsNoData, DataEntryAuditSource.DataEntryType AS DataEntryType, DataEntryAuditSource.CubeViewOrFileName AS CubeViewOrFileName FROM DataEntryAuditCell WITH (NOLOCK) JOIN DataEntryAuditSource ON DataEntryAuditCell.AuditSourceID = DataEntryAuditSource.UniqueID { WhereClause } ORDER BY DataEntryAuditCell.Timestamp DESC "
Dim dt As DataTable Using dbConn As DBConnInfo = BRApi.Database.CreateApplicationDbConnInfo(si) dt = BRAPi.Database.ExecuteSql(dbConn, sql.ToString, ParamsList, False) End Using
'Create new string type columns for dimension descriptions. 'We will replace ID columns with these. Dim Dims As List(Of String) = New List(Of String) For Each dc As DataColumn In dt.Columns Dim ColName As String = dc.ColumnName If ColName.EndsWith("Id") Then Dim DimName As String = ColName.Substring(0, ColName.Length - 2) Dims.Add(DimName) End If Next
For Each DimName In Dims dt.Columns.Add(DimName) Next
'Users taken from audit table rather than BRApi. 'We want to display records also for deleted users. Dim UsersInAuditTable As DataTable = GetUsersFromSecAuditTable(si)
'Get member descriptions for all id columns and user name. 'Use API functions rather than joins. Members table does not contain all member descriptions 'e.g. system dimensions like cons and special cases like None. For Each dr As DataRow In dt.Rows For Each Dimension In Dims If Dimension <> "User" Then Dim IdColName As String = Dimension + "Id"
'DB name for Cons is abbreviated, needs to be changed for dimension type ID lookup. Dim DimensionType = Dimension If Dimension = "Cons" Then DimensionType = "Consolidation" End If
Dim MemberId As Integer = Convert.toInt32(dr(IdColName)) If Dimension = "Cube" Then dr(Dimension) = BRApi.Finance.Cubes.GetCubeInfo(si, MemberId).Cube.Name Else dr(Dimension) = BRApi.Finance.Members.GetMemberName(si, DimType.GetItem(DimensionType).Id, MemberId) End If End If Next
Dim UserID As New Guid If dr("UserId").ToString() IsNot Nothing Then UserID = Guid.Parse(dr("UserId").ToString()) End If
Dim UserRow As DataRow = UsersInAuditTable.Rows.Find(UserID) If UserRow IsNot Nothing Then Dim UserName As String = UserRow.Item("Name") dr("User") = UserName Else dr("User") = "User not found in framework database: " + UserID.ToString() End If Next
'Remove id columns. 'Iterate backwards as altering table indices while looping. For i As Integer = dt.Columns.Count-1 To 0 Step -1 Dim Col As DataColumn = dt.Columns.Item(i) Dim ColName As String = Col.ColumnName If ColName.EndsWith("Id") Then dt.Columns.RemoveAt(i) End If Next
'Order columns for display. dt.Columns("View").SetOrdinal(dt.Columns.Count - 13) dt.Columns("Amount").SetOrdinal(dt.Columns.Count - 1) dt.Columns("PreviousAmount").SetOrdinal(dt.Columns.Count - 1) dt.Columns("IsNoData").SetOrdinal(dt.Columns.Count - 1) dt.Columns("DataEntryType").SetOrdinal(dt.Columns.Count - 1) dt.Columns("CubeViewOrFileName").SetOrdinal(dt.Columns.Count - 1)
Return dt Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, ex)) End Try End Function
Public Function InitDimDict(ByVal si As SessionInfo, substVars As Dictionary(Of String, String)) As DimDictOrError Try Dim Result As New DimDictOrError() Dim DimDict As New Dictionary(Of String, List(Of String))
Dim Dims As List(Of DimType) = DimType.GetAllDimTypes() For Each DimensionType As DimType In Dims
'Get dim and filter expression from parameter. 'Each dimension type has a parameter for both. Dim SelectedDim As String = substVars.XFGetValue($"Select{DimensionType.Name}Dim_OP_DA") Dim MemberFilter As String = substVars.XFGetValue($"Select{DimensionType.Name}_OP_DA")
If MemberFilter <> "" Then Dim MemberStrings As New List(Of String) For Each curDim In BRApi.Finance.Dim.GetDims(si, DimensionType.Id) Dim MemberInfos As List(Of MemberInfo) = BRApi.Finance.Members.GetMembersUsingFilter(si, curDim.DimPk, MemberFilter, True) MemberStrings.AddRange(MemberInfos.Select(Function(m) Convert.ToString(m.Member.MemberId)).ToList()) Next
If MemberStrings.Count = 0 Then Result.isError = True Result.errorMessage = $"{DimensionType} filter didn't return any members. Remember to use proper member filter syntax (e.g. {DimensionType.Abbrev}#MemberName)." Return Result End If
DimDict.Add(DimensionType.Name, MemberStrings) End If
Next
'Cube not in DimTypes, use Cube API. Dim CubeFilter As String = substVars.XFGetValue("SelectCube_OP_DA")
If CubeFilter <> "" Then Dim isError As Boolean = False Dim CubeStrings As New List(Of String)
For Each CubeName As String In CubeFilter.Split(",") CubeName = CubeName.Trim() If Not CubeName.StartsWith("Cb#") Then isError = True Exit For End If CubeName = CubeName.Replace("Cb#", "")
Dim CubeInfoObj As CubeInfo = BRApi.Finance.Cubes.GetCubeInfo(si, CubeName)
If CubeInfoObj Is Nothing Then Continue For CubeStrings.Add(Convert.ToString(CubeInfoObj.Cube.CubeId)) Next
If CubeStrings.Count <> 0 Then DimDict.Add("Cube", CubeStrings) Else isError = True End If
If isError Then Result.isError = True Result.errorMessage = "Cube filter didn't return any members. Remember to use proper member filter syntax (e.g. Cb#MemberName)." Return Result End If End If
Result.DimDict = DimDict Return Result Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, ex)) End Try End Function
Public Function GenerateWhereClauses(si As SessionInfo, DimDict As Dictionary(Of String, List(Of String)), substVars As Dictionary(Of String, String)) As Object Try Dim WhereList As New List(Of String) Dim WhereClause As New Text.StringBuilder
'Parameterize all user inputs (user, date, member filter expressions) for security. Dim ParamsList As New List(Of dbParamInfo)
'Get non-dimension filter parameters. Dim StartDateFilter As String = substVars.XFGetValue("AuditStartDate_OP_DA") Dim EndDateFilter As String = substVars.XFGetValue("AuditEndDate_OP_DA") Dim UserFilter As String = substVars.XFGetValue("User_OP_DA")
'Add non-dimension filter clauses. If UserFilter <> "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000" Then 'User list SQL query needs to use UniqueID which needs to be in this format, placeholder for (All) is '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000' WhereList.Add($"DataEntryAuditSource.UserId = @UserFilter") ParamsList.Add(New DbParamInfo("UserFilter", UserFilter)) End If If StartDateFilter <> "" Then WhereList.Add($"DataEntryAuditCell.Timestamp >= @StartDateFilter") ParamsList.Add(New DbParamInfo("StartDateFilter", StartDateFilter)) End If If EndDateFilter <> "" Then WhereList.Add($"DataEntryAuditCell.Timestamp <= @EndDateFilter") ParamsList.Add(New DbParamInfo("EndDateFilter", EndDateFilter)) End If
'Add dimension filter clauses. For Each kvp As KeyValuePair(Of String, List(Of String)) In DimDict Dim Dimension As String = kvp.Key Dim MemberStrings As List(Of String) = kvp.Value
'DB column name for Consolidation is Cons. If Dimension = "Consolidation" Then Dimension = "Cons" End If
'Parameterize each member ID. Dim Count = 1 Dim ParamNames As New Dictionary(Of String, String) For Each MemberString In MemberStrings ParamNames.Add($"@{Dimension}_{Count}", MemberString) Count += 1 Next Dim InClause As String = String.Join(",", ParamNames.Keys)
WhereList.Add($"{Dimension}Id IN ({InClause})")
For Each ParamName In ParamNames ParamsList.Add(New DbParamInfo(ParamName.Key, ParamName.Value)) Next Next
'Prepare final where clause for query. For Each Condition In WhereList If WhereClause.Length = 0 Then WhereClause.AppendLine($"WHERE {Condition}") Else WhereClause.AppendLine($"AND {Condition}") End If Next
Return New With { .WhereClause = WhereClause.ToString, .ParamsList = ParamsList } Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, ex)) End Try End Function
''' <summary> ''' Gets users from AuditSecUser table rather than BRApi. ''' This table includes also users who have already been removed, ''' if the audit logs haven't been cleared. ''' </summary> ''' <param name="si"></param> ''' <returns>DataTable with primary key on user UniqueId.</returns> Public Function GetUsersFromSecAuditTable(si As SessionInfo) As DataTable Try 'User audit table contains many records for each user, group by id. 'Names can change over time, pick the last occurrance. Dim sql As String = $" SELECT t1.UniqueID, t1.Name, t1.AuditTime FROM AuditSecUser t1 WITH (NOLOCK) JOIN ( SELECT UniqueID, MAX(AuditTime) AuditTime FROM AuditSecUser WITH (NOLOCK) GROUP BY UniqueID ) t2 ON t1.UniqueID = t2.UniqueID AND t1.AuditTime = t2.AuditTime "
Dim dt As DataTable Using dbConn As DBConnInfo = BRApi.Database.CreateFrameworkDbConnInfo(si) dt = BRAPi.Database.ExecuteSql(dbConn, sql.ToString, False) End Using
'Set Guid as primary key, so that table can be queried quickly by user ID. dt.PrimaryKey = New DataColumn() { dt.Columns("UniqueID") }
Return dt
Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, ex)) End Try End Function

#Region "Settings Helpers"
Private Shared Function DropSolutionTables(ByVal si As SessionInfo) As String Try 'Open the DDL script used to create the custom tables required for this solution Dim message As String = ""
If BRApi.Security.Authorization.IsUserInAdminGroup(si) Then 'Get the SQL from the TableDrop file in the dashboard Dim setupFileName As String = "TableDrop_OP_DAT.txt" Dim fileResource As DashboardFileResource = BRApi.Dashboards.FileResources.GetFileResource(si, False, Guid.Empty, setupFileName) If fileResource Is Nothing Then message = "Table Drop File (" & setupFileName & ") is missing or invalid." Else 'Define string to hold SQL table drop script Dim sqlScript As String = Encoding.UTF8.GetString(fileResource.FileBytes)
'Create connection to application database Using dbConnApp As DbConnInfo = BRApi.Database.CreateApplicationDbConnInfo(si) Try 'Create the dashboard Table(s) from the defined script BRApi.Database.ExecuteActionQuery(dbConnApp, sqlScript, False, True)
'Message that tables dropped successfully message = "Solution Tables and Data Uninstalled"
Catch tableEX As Exception 'Message that table drop failed message = "Error: Solution Tables and Data NOT Uninstalled" End Try End Using
End If Else message = "Security Error: Adminstration Rights Required to Execute Uninstall" End If
Return message
Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in DropSolutionTables() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Function
Private Function UninstallSolution(ByVal si As SessionInfo, ByVal args As DashboardExtenderArgs) As XFSelectionChangedTaskResult Try 'Uninstall UI, BRs and Drop Solution Tables Dim solutionCode As String = BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.GetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, "HelpAboutSolutionCode_OP_DAH") Dim selectionChangedTaskResult As New XFSelectionChangedTaskResult() Dim message As New Text.StringBuilder
If BRApi.Security.Authorization.IsUserInAdminGroup(si) Then 'Uninstall the Solution Dim uninstallType As String = args.NameValuePairs.XFGetValue("Type", "UI")
'Evaluate the uninstall type If uninstallType.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("Full") Then 'Drop all associated database tables Dim dropMessage As String = DropSolutionTables(si) message.AppendLine(dropMessage) End If
If uninstallType.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("UI") Or uninstallType.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("Full") Then 'Remove the UI (Maintenance Unit & BRs) Try 'Delete Solution Dashboard Maintenance Unit, all child items of that Dashboard Maintenance Unit and the Dashboard Profile ' BRApi.Dashboards.MaintUnits.DeleteMaintUnit(si, False, args.PrimaryDashboard.MaintUnitID, True) Me.DeleteDMUAndProfile(si, args)
'Delete Solution BR's Me.DropSolutionBRs(si)
'Delete Solution Data Management Groups Me.DropSolutionDM(si, "Data Audit (OP_DA)")
message.AppendLine("User Interface Uninstalled") message.AppendLine("To Complete the Process:") message.AppendLine("1) Close the Dialog") message.AppendLine("2) Close the Dashboard Page")
Catch tableEX As Exception If message.Length = 0 Then message.Append("Error: User Interface & Business Rules NOT Fully Uninstalled.") Else message.AppendLine("Error: User Interface & Business Rules NOT Fully Uninstalled.") End If End Try End If
'Log the Uninstall BRApi.ErrorLog.LogMessage(si, $"Solution ({solutionCode}) was uninstalled [Type: {uninstallType}]{Environment.NewLine}")
Else message.Append("Security Error: Adminstration Rights Required to Execute Uninstall.") End If
'Set the return value selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK = True selectionChangedTaskResult.ShowMessageBox = True selectionChangedTaskResult.Message = message.ToString
Return selectionChangedTaskResult
Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, ex)) End Try End Function
Private Function DropSolutionBRs(ByVal si As SessionInfo) As String Try 'Delete business rules associated with this app Dim message As String = String.Empty Dim dsbBusinessRules As New Dictionary(Of String, BusinessRuleType) From { {"OP_DA_SolutionHelper", BusinessRuleType.DashboardExtender}, {"OP_DA_ParamHelper", BusinessRuleType.DashboardStringFunction}, {"OP_DA_HelperQueries", BusinessRuleType.DashboardDataSet}, {"OP_DA_DataMgmt", BusinessRuleType.Extender} }
If BRApi.Security.Authorization.IsUserInAdminGroup(si) Then Dim frameworkObject As New Framework
'Get/Delete Dashboard Business Rules For Each br As KeyValuePair(Of String, BusinessRuleType) In dsbBusinessRules Dim brInfo As BusinessRuleInfo = frameworkObject.GetBusinessRule(si, False, br.Value, br.Key) If brInfo IsNot Nothing Then frameworkObject.DeleteBusinessRule(si, False, br.Value, br.Key) End If Next Else message = "Security Error: Administration Rights Required to Execute Uninstall." End If
Return message
Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, ex)) End Try
End Function
Private Sub DeleteDMUAndProfile(ByVal si As SessionInfo, ByVal args As DashboardExtenderArgs) Try 'Delete the dashboard profile associated with this solution Dim maintUnit As DashboardMaintUnit = Nothing 'Get the Dashboard Maintenance Unit to delete " + Chr(34) + "XFCS Solution Name (OP_DA)" + Chr(34) + " maintUnit = BRApi.Dashboards.MaintUnits.GetMaintUnit(si, False, args.PrimaryDashboard.WorkspaceID, "Data Audit (OP_DA)") If maintUnit IsNot Nothing Then 'Delete Solution Maintenance and all child items BRApi.Dashboards.MaintUnits.DeleteMaintUnit(si, False, args.PrimaryDashboard.MaintUnitID, True) End If
'Delete Solution Dashboard Profile Using dbConnApp As DbConnInfo = BRApi.Database.CreateApplicationDbConnInfo(si) Using dbConnFW As DbConnInfo = BRApi.Database.CreateFrameworkDbConnInfo(si) Dim dashProfile As DashboardProfile = Nothing dashProfile = EngineDashboardProfiles.GetProfile(dbConnApp, "Data Audit (OP_DA)") If dashProfile IsNot Nothing Then SecurityHelperWcf.ValidateDelete(dbConnFW, dbConnApp, DashboardHelperWcf.GetRoleType(True), dashProfile, throwOnError:=True) EngineDashboardProfiles.DeleteProfile(dbConnApp, dashProfile.UniqueID) End If End Using End Using
Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, ex)) End Try End Sub
Private Sub DropSolutionDM(ByVal si As SessionInfo, Optional groupName As String = "") Try 'Delete data management associated with this app Using dbConnFramework As DbConnInfo = BRApi.Database.CreateFrameworkDbConnInfo(si) Using dbConnApp As DbConnInfo = BRApi.Database.CreateApplicationDbConnInfo(si)
Dim dmGroupId As Guid = Guid.Empty 'Get UniqueID for the DataMgmtGroup to be removed Dim dmGroups As List(Of DataMgmtGroup) = DataMgmtProfilesWcf.GetAllGroups(dbConnFramework, dbConnApp) If Not String.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(groupName) Then For Each Group As DataMgmtGroup In dmGroups If Group.Name = groupName Then dmGroupId = Group.UniqueID End If Next End If
If Not dmGroupId = Guid.Empty Then 'Delete DataMgmtSequence Dim sequences As List(Of DataMgmtSequence) = DataMgmtSequencesWcf.GetSequencesInGroup(dbConnFramework, dbConnApp, dmGroupId) For Each dmSequence As DataMgmtSequence In sequences DataMgmtSequencesWcf.DeleteSequence(dbConnFramework, dbConnApp, dmSequence.UniqueID) Next
'Delete DataMgmtSeqStepMember Dim steps As List(Of DataMgmtStepSummaryInfo) = DataMgmtStepsWcf.GetStepsInGroup(dbConnFramework, dbConnApp, dmGroupId) For Each dmStep As DataMgmtStepSummaryInfo In steps DataMgmtStepsWcf.DeleteStep(dbConnFramework, dbConnApp, dmStep.UniqueID) Next
' Delete the DataMgmtGroup DataMgmtProfilesWcf.DeleteGroup(dbConnFramework, dbConnApp, dmGroupId) End If
End Using End Using Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in DropSolutionDM() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Sub
Private Function CreateStandardTables(ByVal si As SessionInfo) As XFSelectionChangedTaskResult Try Dim selectionChangedTaskResult As New XFSelectionChangedTaskResult()
Using dbConnApp As DbConnInfo = BRApi.Database.CreateApplicationDbConnInfo(si) If Not DbSql.DoesTableExist(dbConnApp, "XFW_OP_DA_ControlLists") Then Dim SetupFileName As String = "TableSetup_OP_DAT.txt" Dim fileResource As DashboardFileResource = BRApi.Dashboards.FileResources.GetFileResource(si, False, Guid.Empty, SetupFileName) If fileResource Is Nothing Then selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK = False selectionChangedTaskResult.ShowMessageBox = True selectionChangedTaskResult.Message = $"Table Setup File ({SetupFileName}) is missing or invalid." Return selectionChangedTaskResult End If
Try Dim sqlScript As String = Encoding.UTF8.GetString(fileResource.FileBytes) BRApi.Database.ExecuteActionQuery(dbConnApp, sqlScript, False, True) selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK = True selectionChangedTaskResult.ShowMessageBox = True selectionChangedTaskResult.Message = "Setup Completed"
Catch TableEX As Exception 'Message that tables creation failed selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK = False selectionChangedTaskResult.ShowMessageBox = True selectionChangedTaskResult.Message = "Error: Solution Tables NOT Created" End Try Else 'Nothing to do selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK = True selectionChangedTaskResult.ShowMessageBox = True selectionChangedTaskResult.Message = "Setup Completed" End If Return selectionChangedTaskResult End Using Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in CreateStandardTables() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Function
Private Function GetCurrentVersionDataTable(ByVal si As SessionInfo) As DataTable Try Dim OP_DA_CurrentVersion As Integer = GetCurrentVersionFromDashboardParam(si) 'Define the SQL Statement Dim sql As String = $"Select * From XFW_OP_DA_ControlLists Where ListName = '{OP_DA_CurrentVersion}'"
'Return the DataTable 'Create Standard Resource Tables Using dbConnApp As DbConnInfo = BRApi.Database.CreateApplicationDbConnInfo(si) If (DbSql.DoesTableExist(dbConnApp, "XFW_OP_DA_ControlLists")) Then Return BRApi.Database.ExecuteSql(dbConnApp, sql, False) End If End Using Return Nothing
Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in GetCurrentVersionDataTable() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Function
Private Function GetCurrentSolutionVersion(ByVal si As SessionInfo) As Integer Try Dim currentVersion As Integer = SharedConstants.Unknown 'Return the DataTable Using dt As DataTable = GetCurrentVersionDataTable(si) If dt IsNot Nothing Then If dt.Rows.Count = 1 Then currentVersion = ConvertHelper.ToInt32(dt(0)("StoredValue")) End If End If End Using Return currentVersion Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in GetCurrentVersionDataTable() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Function
Public Function GetCurrentVersionFromDashboardParam(ByVal si As SessionInfo) As Integer Try Dim version As Integer = SharedConstants.Unknown Dim dbParamVersion As String = BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.GetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, "HelpAboutVersion_OP_DAH") Dim pv As String = String.Empty Dim sv As String = String.Empty
'Param Version should be in XXX PV440 SV100 format. If Not String.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(dbParamVersion) Then Dim mc As RegularExpressions.MatchCollection = Regex.Matches(dbParamVersion, "^.*PV(\d+)-SV(\d+)") If mc.Count > 0 Then Dim m As System.Text.RegularExpressions.Match = mc(0) pv = m.Groups(1).Value sv = m.Groups(2).Value Else Throw New XFUserMsgException(si, Nothing, Nothing, "Error: Solution Version Invalid") End If Else Throw New XFUserMsgException(si, Nothing, Nothing, "Error: Solution Version Invalid") End If
'Each Version Should be 3 Characters. Validate/Error if this isn't True. If (Not pv.Length = 3) Or (Not sv.Length = 3) Then Throw New XFUserMsgException(si, Nothing, Nothing, "Error: Solution Version Invalid") End If
version = ConvertHelper.ToInt32(pv & sv)
Return version
Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in GetCurrentVersionFromDashboardParam() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Function
Private Function CreateSolutionTables(ByVal si As SessionInfo, ByVal args As DashboardExtenderArgs) As XFSelectionChangedTaskResult Try 'Create or Upgrade the solution schema Dim selectionChangedTaskResult As New XFSelectionChangedTaskResult()
'Validate Setup is not a downgrade Dim prevVersion As Integer = GetCurrentSolutionVersion(si) Dim currentVersion As Integer = GetCurrentVersionFromDashboardParam(si) If (prevVersion > currentVersion) And (prevVersion <> SharedConstants.Unknown) Then Dim solutionCode As String = BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.GetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, "HelpAboutSolutionCode_OP_DAH") Throw New XFUserMsgException(si, Nothing, Nothing, StringHelper.FormatMessage("Critical Error: Setup Aborted. Unable to downgrade from {0} {1} to {0} {2} without first executing a full uninstall or {0} {1}.", solutionCode, prevVersion, currentVersion)) End If
'Create Standard Tables to hold version info and settings selectionChangedTaskResult = CreateStandardTables(si)
'New Install (Create Tables and Return) 'If IsOk Is returned Then, the table was created As a New install - Return the result If selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK Then ' Update the default dashboard UpdateDefaultDashBoard(si, args, selectionChangedTaskResult) 'Update Stored Current Version StoreCurrentSolutionVersion(si, currentVersion) 'Attempt to Reset the Old Global Settings if they exist RestoreLastSaveGlobalOptions(si)
Return selectionChangedTaskResult End If Return selectionChangedTaskResult Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in CreateSolutionTables() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Function
Private Shared Sub UpdateDefaultDashBoard(ByVal si As SessionInfo, ByRef args As DashboardExtenderArgs, ByRef selectionChangedTaskResult As XFSelectionChangedTaskResult) Try 'Get values for passed parameter Dim defaultPage As String = args.NameValuePairs.XFGetValue("DefaultPage", SharedConstants.Unknown.ToString) 'Set dashboardDB to Open BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.SetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, "MainDashboardName_OP_DAS", defaultPage) selectionChangedTaskResult.ChangeCustomSubstVarsInDashboard = True args.SelectionChangedTaskInfo.CustomSubstVars("MainDashboardName_OP_DAS") = defaultPage selectionChangedTaskResult.ModifiedCustomSubstVars = args.SelectionChangedTaskInfo.CustomSubstVars Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in UpdateDefaultDashBoard() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Sub
Private Function GetSettingsStorageForUpgradeDataTable(ByVal si As SessionInfo, Optional ByVal storedSettingsTableGroup As String = "") As DataTable Try Dim XFW_LastSavedSettings As String = GetCurrentVersionFromDashboardParam(si) 'Define the SQL Statement Dim sql As String = String.Empty If storedSettingsTableGroup = "All" Then sql = $"SELECT * FROM XFW_OP_DA_ControlLists WHERE ListName = 'XFW_OP_DA_GlobalSettings' OR ListName = 'XFW_OP_DA_LCRSettings' OR ListName = 'XFW_OP_DA_MFBSettings' AND StoredValue = '{XFW_LastSavedSettings}'" Else sql = $"SELECT * From XFW_OP_DA_ControlLists WHERE ListName = '{storedSettingsTableGroup}' AND StoredValue = '{XFW_LastSavedSettings}'" End If
'Return the DataTable Using dbConnApp As DbConnInfo = BRApi.Database.CreateApplicationDbConnInfo(si) Return BRApi.Database.ExecuteSql(dbConnApp, sql, False) End Using
Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in GetSettingsStorageForUpgradeDataTable() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Function
Private Sub RestoreLastSaveGlobalOptions(ByVal si As SessionInfo) Try 'Get the last stored settings value string in the Control tables and update the Literal Parameters Using dt As DataTable = Me.GetSettingsStorageForUpgradeDataTable(si, "All") If dt IsNot Nothing Then If dt.Rows.Count > 0 Then 'Get the last stored settings values and update the global options For Each settingsRow As DataRow In dt.Rows Dim dr As DataRow = settingsRow Dim nvb As New NameValueFormatBuilder(CType(dr("DisplayValue"), String)) 'Loop over the name value pairs and update the corresponding literal parameters If nvb IsNot Nothing Then For Each kvp As KeyValuePair(Of String, String) In nvb.NameValuePairs BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.SetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, kvp.Key, kvp.Value) Next End If Next End If End If End Using
Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in RestoreLastSaveGlobalOptions() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Sub
Private Sub StoreCurrentSolutionVersion(ByVal si As SessionInfo, ByVal version As Integer) Try Using dt As DataTable = Me.GetCurrentVersionDataTable(si) Dim OP_DA_CurrentVersion As Integer = GetCurrentVersionFromDashboardParam(si) If dt IsNot Nothing Then If dt.Rows.Count = 0 Then 'NEW: Store the last setup version Dim dr As DataRow = dt.NewRow dr("ListName") = OP_DA_CurrentVersion dr("StoredValue") = version.ToString dr("DisplayValue") = version.ToString dr("Description") = si.UserName dr("Active") = False dt.Rows.Add(dr) Else 'Update: Store the last setup version Dim dr As DataRow = dt.Rows(0) dr.BeginEdit() dr("ListName") = OP_DA_CurrentVersion dr("StoredValue") = version.ToString dr("DisplayValue") = version.ToString dr("Description") = si.UserName dr("Active") = False dr.EndEdit() End If
'Execute the save BRApi.Database.SaveCustomDataTable(si, "App", "XFW_OP_DA_ControlLists", dt, False) End If End Using
Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in StoreCurrentSolusionVersion() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Sub
Public Sub AddOrUpdateDictionary(ByRef modifiedVars As Dictionary(Of String, String), key As String, value As String) If (modifiedVars.ContainsKey(key)) Then modifiedVars(key) = value Else modifiedVars.Add(key, value) End If End Sub
Private Sub SetDashboards(ByVal si As SessionInfo, ByVal solutionCode As String, ByRef modifiedVars As Dictionary(Of String, String), Optional ByVal parameterName As String = Nothing, Optional ByVal dashboardName As String = Nothing) Try
AddOrUpdateDictionary(modifiedVars, "Toolbar_OP_DA", "2_Toolbar_OP_DA" & solutionCode) AddOrUpdateDictionary(modifiedVars, "SelectedContentDashboard_OP_DA", "3_Content_OP_DA" & solutionCode)
If (Not String.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(dashboardName) AndAlso Not String.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(parameterName)) Then AddOrUpdateDictionary(modifiedVars, parameterName, dashboardName) End If Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in SetDashboards() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Sub
Private Function ValidateSetupStepsExecuted(ByVal si As SessionInfo, ByVal args As DashboardExtenderArgs) As XFSelectionChangedTaskResult Try 'Validate that the user has executed the setup steps '---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Dim selectionChangedTaskResult As New XFSelectionChangedTaskResult() Dim mainDashboardName As String = args.NameValuePairs.XFGetValue("MainDashboardName", SharedConstants.Unknown.ToString) Dim modifiedVars As New Dictionary(Of String, String)
'If the user executed the setup steps, the MainDashboardName will no longer equal the name of the setup dashboard Dim setupDashboardName As String = "0_Frame_OP_DAT" If mainDashboardName.XFEqualsIgnoreCase(setupDashboardName) Then 'User has NOT executed the setup steps selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK = False selectionChangedTaskResult.ShowMessageBox = True selectionChangedTaskResult.Message = "Please execute all required setup steps prior to launching the solution" selectionChangedTaskResult.ChangeSelectionChangedNavigationInDashboard = True selectionChangedTaskResult.ModifiedSelectionChangedNavigationInfo.SelectionChangedNavigationType = XFSelectionChangedNavigationType.NoAction selectionChangedTaskResult.ModifiedSelectionChangedNavigationInfo.SelectionChangedNavigationArgs = "" Else 'Launch the page selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK = True selectionChangedTaskResult.ShowMessageBox = False SetDashboards(si, "", modifiedVars, "SelectedContent_OP_DA", "3_Content_OP_DAM") selectionChangedTaskResult.ChangeCustomSubstVarsInDashboard = True selectionChangedTaskResult.ModifiedCustomSubstVars = modifiedVars selectionChangedTaskResult.ChangeSelectionChangedNavigationInDashboard = True selectionChangedTaskResult.ModifiedSelectionChangedNavigationInfo.SelectionChangedNavigationType = XFSelectionChangedNavigationType.OpenPage selectionChangedTaskResult.ModifiedSelectionChangedNavigationInfo.SelectionChangedNavigationArgs = "XFPage=Dashboard:0_Frame_OP_DA_OnePlace" End If Return selectionChangedTaskResult
Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in ValidateSetupStepsExecuted() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Function
